    • registrationData

      @DataProvider(name="registrationData") public java.lang.Object[][] registrationData​(org.testng.ITestContext context)
      DataProvider Annotation from testing framework support data-driven testing, which allows you to automatically run a test case multiple times with different input and validation values. When you need to pass complex parameters or parameters that need to be created from Java (complex objects, objects read from a flat files(CSV,EXCEL,Property,...) or a database, etcâ€¦). in such cases parameters can be passed using Dataproviders. A Data Provider is a method annotated with @DataProvider. A Data Provider returns an 2D array of objects. using ITestContext to get fileExtension , fileName form testngSuite.xml to run suitable file from test data file directory
      Parameters:
      context - to pass parameters (DataSizeRow,DataSizeCol,fileExtension,fileName) from testngSuite.xml to data_provider which in turn pass them to HelperClass reading data from external file
      Returns:
      test data to use them into my tests conncted to this data_provider method
